The paper deals with image processing and recognition, specifically in the context of flower images. This suggests that it could fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of Support Vector Machines (SVM) for image retrieval suggests that it could also fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of color features, which could place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of shape features and moment invariants suggests that it could also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning methods such as SVM suggests that it could also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
